values:
I just had a really good discussion with Alex...about stuff I dont' talk to anyone about.

Weird.

Tonight was a lot of fun....for the most part.

I have no justification for being so upset about things but I still am. I expect better of you than I do of me, yet you have fucked up so many times that is not reasonable.

My MRI went well. I listened to Michael Buble (how do you spell it?). The guy who did it was real old.

I don't get it. 

ps my current music obsession is voxtrot/the weepies. yes.

I had the blankest year
I saw life turn into a TV show
It was totally weird
The person I knew I didn't really know


weiiiird

I am glad to be home, but not too thrilled about classes (though I haven't been to one yet).

Also, this globally warmed winter we are having is quite lovely since I have no cute warm clothes.
Why does just talking to you absolutely infuriate me?
would it be immature to dance around singing "liar liar pants on fire" like one of my students?

And why would it be smiling? Because you glare. Yes, the penguin glare makes me smile.

As does the sun coming out JUST for me at the gardens :)

and this ridiculous techno Molly is playing.

I enrolled in classes for next semester, though I didn't get all that I wanted.

A month from today (or yesterday?) I move to austin for the summer

eek, almost not a freshman anymore.

Sometimes my motherly instinct kicks in just a little too much and i worry myself into the ground.

On the bright side some mexicans said "hola" to me in target today because i am sooo cute.

I know I'm alone if I'm with or without you
but just being around you offers me another form of relief


Merry Christmas, loves.
I want to play with a light bright.

Syrupy alcohol makes me feel warm inside but it also makes me sick.

I am so unsettled.
Moral of the story: I always win. Always.
I think I have come to depend upon the wrong people, and it confuses me so.

Whoever said there is beauty in the breakdown was a liar.

Although apparently I am poetic, but only in my death.

I am in an odd mood and I have the urge to tell everyone exactly what I think of them.

I am very certain I would regret this decision though, so I shall restrain myself.

Freakin' Say Anything concert and girls night/slumber party tomorrow. 

I am so hungry. I want a job so I can go get some freakin' food. And I want to be in Austin so I can get that  food at Kerby or Mag. I go back and forth on this a lot...more forth than back though.

I am going to forget my appointment tomorrow. I must remember.

I I I I I I. Thats all this entry said. Oh well ,its my freakin' online journal. 

Also, I really hate blue octobers new stuff. It sucks. 

"I hate everything about you, why do I love you" That line will not stop running through my head and I cannot for the life of me remember the last time I heard the song, or what the song is...damn...

I finally called and made an appointment with the student health center today for Thursday afternoon so I can face my deamons and finally get some sleep.

I don't know what will happen but I do know it scares the shit out of me.

Livejournal has undergone a transformation for pirate day.


heck yes.

classes start tomorrow. we'll see how this goes.


In heaven everything is fine, you've got your way and I've got mine.

I have more stuff than I know what to do with

I think if have everything for my dorm....except laundry stuff...crap i knew i was forgetting something, oh well.

this afternoon is for packing and cleaning

tonight i get to see my boy, i am excited. I missed him.

gah i love high school musical

I found out today that next year i will be residing in Bruce room C310 with a girl named Molly.

yay i am going to college and i have a place to stay and someone to stay there with!

oh and Afua made me UNT friends, woohoo! 

and we move in on a sunday....what is that?!?

This will be a +/- entry because i am lazy and its my journal so i can do what i want...so there

+going to see Danny's band this afternoon
--------------- my grandma is back in the hospital
-- have crazy stomach pains from hell
----+Corbet is out of town for the next week
++++my lover comes back from the beach tomorrow

i am exhausted. bed time. it will be a long/amazing/bad/fun week

Schwartzy told us a story today about how a lady got eaten by an alligator last week in Florida while jogging. The alligator ate her arms and smashed her head/chest and then hid her in its little alligator house. They killed the alligator and found her arms....

I don't know what that had to do with what we were "learning" but i do not think i will be going jogging in florida anytime soon....

I got several of the reviews for my finals today, the are either too vague to be any help or too long to be any help....so yay...

I do not feel good. I love am done with today, it can be tomorrow now.....

I am also done with May. Bye may, see ya next year!

Afua just told me we should take a blank check to orientation, well now that sounds fun!!!

I know, I'll start studying tonight/reading reading lolita in tehran so i can do well on them.....

hah, sure i will.

They played the fray today on the annoucements and when coach turned off the TV everyone kept singing, made me kinda sad.... they never sing for the cool songs.... :(

Comment on this entry and I will give you a letter. Write ten words beginning with that letter in your journal, including an explanation what the word means to you and why, and than pass out letters to those who want to play along.

Laura as assigned me M....my words will not be as amusing as hers were though, just a warning...

1. Monday- Well, it is monday and i hate mondays. It is rare that something good happens on a monday, except for I turn 18 on a monday i think...that will be good...i also like the song manic monday but the cool punk version :)
2. Money- this is another thing i am not overly fond of....seriously, why can't it just grow on trees?
3. Math- I am not in a math this year and i enjoy listening to everyone who is complain about it and know that for this year i don't have to worry about it, although i am fairly good at math so i don't know why i'm not in it...
4. Mob- Contorno went to be part of the mob of protestors today, i wish pool was cool like him...freaking kids who have contorno!
5. May- Well it is now May. We graduate this month. we take ap test. we take our final. college people come home. we have all our graduation stuff. my soulmate turns 18. my auntie comes from seattle twice. It is going to be a busy month!!
6. mollusca- we are studying this phylum in aquatic science right now...or maybe we just finished it and are starting on another one...i do not know really but i do know i have to know a lot about this phylum come friday so i can do well on my test. I think it includes crabs but i could be mistaken....
7. Mistakes- theres another word. We all make them, but i don't think we should dwell on our mistakes. shit happens. move on with life.
8. Monetary- this is one of the policies i learned for the economics test last monday although i cannot remember it to save my life today, only a week later
9. memory- clearly i have a bad one. This is not true, it is just very selective and only remembers things that are of absolutely no use to me. Lyrics to a spice girls song from 4th grade? You bet! Random inside jokes? Of course! Economics? Oh hell no!
10. malapropism- this was one of our vocab words meaning the extreme misuse of a word. I balled the vocab test and i just like the word so i thought i'd throw it in there!!


19 school days left....24 normal days....2 ap tests....i only have 2 finals during finals week (only 1 of them i am counting as being a real final).....oh school is oh so close to being over and i'm not sure how i feel about that fact anymore

Morgan and I were working on her end of the year slideshow today in photography and she is doing one to play at her grad party...we were sitting there going through the pics and I noticed one that had a much younger jamie and was slightly amused for a moment until i noticed mrs rowley was sitting on the couch smiling in the picture....it was after she got sick...i started to cry

i don't know, leaving soon is making me miss things.....

Today was very good

much much better than yesterdeay

morgan, abby, casey and i heard coach hutchens perform

he is actually very good

we are doing it again

it was a lot of fun!

yaaaay!

strike that

i don't need cigarettes, really i don't

i have really amazing friends who always seem to cheer me

so yay :)

i really could not ask for more

I signed up for orientation

everyone go to the 5th session....July 12-14

all the cool kids are doing it

except afua

yeah....I'm going to college...in 4 months and 1 day

scary

So. Life is really good. I like it a lot, but it should be mid-May right about now......

The trip to Port A. was really fun, but I was very glad to get home. 

7 girls all roomed together, rode together, bonded in the bathroom together and did everything together and we didn't kill each other! Go us! We rule!

Umm....I have pictures....but I am lazy, so maybe later.

Got up and went to the sunrise service and then went to breakfast/hung out. It was worth getting up for.

Did I mention life is good? :)

Theres been times i'm so confused all my roads they lead to you, just can't turn and walk away. Its hard to say what it is i see in you wonder if i'll always be with you. Words can't say and I can't do enough to prove it's all for you.

that song usually cheers me up. didn't work this time though.


I need a break. I hate money.

Anyone up for a roadtrip whatever weekend is closest to April the 20th?

Hi. I am not dating Corbet. kthanks.

Dinner with my soulmate was wonderful

annnnd Corey is back at razzoos and we went and visited him

annnnnnnd some people frustrated me greatly tonight

that is all.

ps i'm sorry for reposting...but sadly it made me laugh

YOU KNOW YOU'RE FROM ANDERSON WHEN...

1.only seniors leaving campus is the biggest joke ever
2.you hear daily of some dumbshit jumping off the third floor and breaking something
3. you hear about 2 black girls gettin beaten down in the stair well
4. you hear on the news about a coach fuckin a student.
5. you hear the saying "we are not a good school but a great school" and it reminds you of kernwine (sp)
6. you hear weekly that some fuckin dumb ass freackin runs into the milk machine to break the glass to get free milk
7. "uuuuhhhh" is a regular installment in the announcements on the pa system
8. you see the parking lot monitor telling the underclassmen to "be safe" as they're going off campus for lunch
9. we already know the outcome of the football games before we even know who we're playing
10. there are at least 5 parties EVERY weekend
11. monday mornings are dedicated to hearing about "how totally wasted" everyone got that weekend
12. you're more proud of your dance team AND cheer squad than of the football team
13. you hear about people having sex in the bathroom and dont think anything of it

14. when you correct the spelling on stuff other people have posted
15. when you know all your teachers' favorite RANTS by heart (and know what will set them off)
16. you've ever signed up to talk to your counselor just so you can skip class
17. cheating doesn't count unless you get caught AND can't talk your way out of it
18. the huge plans for a sprinkler system result only in a massive mud puddle
19. you know the student's code (of conduct) is more GUIDELINES, than actual rules
20. you know that dona aixa's spanish class is "attended by the damned and taught by a woman SO EVIL that Hell itself spat her back out"
21. you realize that SLEEP IS FOR THE WEAK!
22. you write more in your fine arts class than in english
23. you know that if you get caught going against the crowd in the stairwell, you may never make it to class.
24. you dont hesitate to correct you teacher, and then comment on how stupid their mistake was
25. you dont understand how Stealth can be so slow, and yet so...stealthy
27. you can smell overachievers
28. you stop doing all work becuase it's faster and easier to cheat. plus, you make better grades
29. you remember what a JOKE SLC was
30. you live off TacoShack
31. you have enough school t-shirts to clothe a small army
32. you realised there is no number 26 on this list
33. you've got the art of wasting class time down to a science
34. you know sweatshirts only come with hoods so you can cover your headphones
35. you can buy any drug you want without ever getting off your bus
36. everyone has a theory about which teachers are on which drugs
37. you can remember getting to school 20 minutes late and having to wait at the TARDY TABLE for 20 more, so you could go to the last 3 minutes of class
38. only two of your teachers ask for your permit to enter, and then when you dont have it, they give you detention...
39. but you dont care because detention is just teacher-speak for study hall
40. you've run into a locked bathroom door
41. you've fallen down the stairs when they were covered in an inch of water cuz its raining
42. you dress in layers so you can deal with the 50 degree temperature difference from the classrooms to the corridors
43. you can sing the quadratic formula
44. know mega boost days mean half the people wont show up, and those that do, wont do shit
45. the only part of morning announcements that you listen to are the songs...
46. ...and maybe not even that
47. you've tried to high-five a swimmer and been told to shove it up your ass (jk reed we <3 you)
48. know substitutes are inately incapable of working movie projectors
49. you're not surprised when you hear that someone got in trouble for riding a unicycle in the hallway. you just laugh
50. you dont know any of the words to the school song, but you've nearly lost your pinky fingers while mubling it at a pep rally

So, has anybody studied yet? I sure haven't. And i lost my binder with all my assignements in it....poop.

This year has gone by so amazingly fast. For the most part it has been simply amazing. Finally being a senior, having an amazing experience in mexico, first love and all that jazz. There have been a few really low points such as losing my grandfather and first love, but it really made me realize how wonderful my friends are. I love them and will miss them terribly when we all go our seperate ways in 8 months.

Anna and I talked about college today. I really love the idea of driving to San Francisco with her, it sounds like it'd be a lovely trip and not too long after Seattle either. I am so excited about this coming up summer. I'm not sure it could top this past summer....but it's looking like it could sure give it a run for it's money! Of course it'll also have getting ready to leave and stuff....sheesh, we're all growing up so fast. Some days I just want to curl up and watch Little House on the Prarie or make up mean songs about large people (before I realized how wrong it was). I don't know...sometimes life is just funny and it changes so fast but most of us grow and learn and adapt and i sware i'm shutting up now

1 week girls till the ultimate senior bonding!!!
